---
// src/components/StrategicDeepDive.astro
---
<section class="py-24 bg-[#0B1120] text-white relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full bg-[url('/grid.svg')] opacity-5 pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 right-0 w-[500px] h-[500px] bg-blue-900/10 rounded-full blur-[100px] pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative z-10">
        
        <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-20">
    <h2 class="text-blue-400 font-bold tracking-widest text-xs uppercase mb-4">
        The Reality Check
    </h2>
    <h3 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white mb-6">
        Questions smart owners ask. <br>
        <span class="text-slate-500">And the honest answers.</span>
    </h3>
    <p class="text-slate-400 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        You’ve built a successful business. You are skeptical of "magic bullets." We respect that. Here is the truth about owned assets vs. rented land.
    </p>
</div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            
            <div class="group relative bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-3xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm hover:border-purple-500/50 transition-all duration-300">
                <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-500/10 to-transparent opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity rounded-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>
                
                <div class="relative z-10">
                    <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-6">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-slate-800 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-slate-700 group-hover:border-purple-500/50 group-hover:bg-purple-900/20 transition-colors">
                            <i data-lucide="instagram" class="w-6 h-6 text-slate-400 group-hover:text-purple-400"></i>
                        </div>
                        <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-purple-500/10 text-purple-300 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full border border-purple-500/20">Social Media</span>
                    </div>

                    <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">"I get clients from Instagram. Why do I need a website?"</h4>
                    
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <p class="text-purple-200 text-sm font-medium">
                            Social Media is "Attention". Google is "Intention".
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-white/5 pt-4">
                            People scroll Instagram to kill time. They search Google to solve a problem. <br><br>
                            When a client searches <em>"Anxiety Therapy Subang"</em>, they are holding their credit card, ready to book. That is the <strong>high-intent traffic</strong> you are currently missing.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="group relative bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-3xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm hover:border-yellow-500/50 transition-all duration-300">
                <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-yellow-500/10 to-transparent opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity rounded-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>
                
                <div class="relative z-10">
                    <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-6">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-slate-800 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-slate-700 group-hover:border-yellow-500/50 group-hover:bg-yellow-900/20 transition-colors">
                            <i data-lucide="star" class="w-6 h-6 text-slate-400 group-hover:text-yellow-400"></i>
                        </div>
                        <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-yellow-500/10 text-yellow-300 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full border border-yellow-500/20">Reputation</span>
                    </div>

                    <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">"I have 1,000+ Google Reviews. Why do I need this?"</h4>
                    
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <p class="text-yellow-200 text-sm font-medium">
                            Reviews are your Reputation. Stegg is your Reach.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-white/5 pt-4">
                            Your reviews are amazing, but they are stuck on a "leash." Google Maps prioritizes distance. If a customer is 8km away, Google hides you—no matter how many stars you have.<br><br>
                            Stegg puts you in front of people who are <strong>too far for the Map</strong>, but willing to travel for quality.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="group relative bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-3xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm hover:border-blue-500/50 transition-all duration-300">
                <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500/10 to-transparent opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity rounded-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>
                
                <div class="relative z-10">
                    <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-6">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-slate-800 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-slate-700 group-hover:border-blue-500/50 group-hover:bg-blue-900/20 transition-colors">
                            <i data-lucide="map" class="w-6 h-6 text-slate-400 group-hover:text-blue-400"></i>
                        </div>
                        <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-500/10 text-blue-300 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full border border-blue-500/20">Synergy</span>
                    </div>

                    <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">"Will this help my Google Map ranking too?"</h4>
                    
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <p class="text-blue-200 text-sm font-medium">
                            Yes. It acts as a signal flare to Google.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-white/5 pt-4">
                            Google looks for "Prominence." When our pages start driving traffic from neighborhoods like <em>Mont Kiara</em> to your site, it signals: <em class="italic text-slate-300">"This business is relevant to that neighborhood."</em><br><br>
                            This organic traffic helps <strong>stretch your Map radius</strong>.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="group relative bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-3xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm hover:border-green-500/50 transition-all duration-300">
                <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500/10 to-transparent opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity rounded-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>
                
                <div class="relative z-10">
                    <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-6">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-slate-800 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-slate-700 group-hover:border-green-500/50 group-hover:bg-green-900/20 transition-colors">
                            <i data-lucide="check-circle-2" class="w-6 h-6 text-slate-400 group-hover:text-green-400"></i>
                        </div>
                        <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-green-500/10 text-green-300 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full border border-green-500/20">The Logic</span>
                    </div>

                    <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">"Does this really work? It sounds too simple."</h4>
                    
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <p class="text-green-200 text-sm font-medium">
                            It works because it's boring math.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-white/5 pt-4">
                            Google is a robot. It wants to give the searcher the exact match. If someone searches "Service + Location", and you have a page titled exactly <strong>"Service + Location"</strong>, you mathematically beat a generic "Home" page.<br><br>
                            We just automate the "boring work" of creating those perfect matches.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</section>